dismissalText.commentary: David Hussey run out (NLTC Perera) 34 (39b 1x4 0x6 76m) SR: 87.17

dismissalComment.html: Perera has conjured another wicket - a run out this time. Hussey hit that straight into the pitch and took off for a run that simply wasn't there, because the ball had only made it as far as the bowler. Hussey turned to return to his crease, but Perera was on target with the throw and Hussey was miles out. Decent knock there from Hussey. The end of a very good partnership.
Dilshan is being mobbed by his team-mates, lovely delivery, angled in on a good length from round the stumps, pitches off, and straightens sharply to beat Warner's push and hit the stump

another slower ball, an full. Maxwell trying to smash that over the top, but he's undone by the lack of pace again, and this time the top edge sails high enough for a fielder to settle under it at extra cover.

dismissalText.commentary: David Warner b Dilshan 10 (18b 1x4 0x6 22m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: Dilshan is being mobbed by his team-mates, lovely delivery, angled in on a good length from round the stumps, pitches off, and straightens sharply to beat Warner's push and hit the stump

dismissalText.commentary: Matthew Wade lbw b Kulasekara 23 (28b 4x4 0x6 36m) SR: 82.14

dismissalComment.html: OUT! Second breakthrough for Sri Lanka, and no, this one isn't the outswinger to the left handers. Kulasekara pitches it on leg and gets it to straighten, which is what does Wade in. the batsman had expected that to go with the angle and played a delicate cut shot, but the ball struck him in front and the review could not save him.

dismissalText.commentary: George Bailey c & b NLTC Perera 17 (43b 1x4 0x6 67m) SR: 39.53

dismissalComment.html: would you believe it? Perera has conjured a wicket out of nowhere. Fullish ball, seemed to hang in the pitch for a moment and Bailey was too quick on the shot. He ends up lobbing that straight back to the bowler, who takes a decent catch, bending low on his follow through.

dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews c Bailey b Johnson 67 (79b 7x4 0x6 122m) SR: 84.81

dismissalComment.html: Gone! And that could be it for Sri Lanka! Slower ball bouncer from Johnson and Mathews can't time that one. Lobs off the splice to midwicket, who completes an easy take.

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene c Starc b Doherty 38 (39b 6x4 0x6 55m) SR: 97.43

dismissalComment.html: that was somewhat out of the blue. Seems to have stuck in the pitch more than Mahela expected. He was aiming a shot through mid off, but gets an inside edge and it lobs to mid on, who takes a simple catch. Doherty delivers the breakthrough Australia needed.

poor option from Thirimanne, and Sri Lanka are throwing away a decent start. He came down the pitch and tried to loft that over midwicket, only he hit it too straight and David Hussey at long on ran around to swallow it. It was the result of some good pressure, but he will feel that that shot wasn't called for, so early in his innings

commentTextItems.html: slower again, and gone. Malinga pokes at that one and it lobs off the bat and into the hands of short third man, who takes a good low catch.

commentPostTextItems.html: This series is shared, but there's more to come from the tour, when the first of two Twenty20s kicks off on the 26th at the SCG. Join us then for more commentary.

Looks like we can't bring the presentation to you today, but thanks for being with us. If I can hazard a guess I'd say Phil Hughes will win the man of the match, and Nuwan Kulasekara is the player of the series, but Hughes has an outside shot of taking that out too. Those would by my two picks anyway.

Dylan: "If you had to blame a period of Sri Lanka inning for the defeat, blame the 10 over block, the 17th to 26th over. 18 runs for 2 wickets in this section stalled their innings and caused unnecessary pressure to build. An extra 25 runs here would have helped."

So Australia have leveled it up. Mahela may feel he chose wrongly at the toss, given how difficult the pitch became for scoring in the second innings. Not the ideal send-off for him as captain, but he has been a terrific leader for Sri Lanka and he's got the team to a better place than he found it.

commentTextItems.html: loses control of that one, down the leg side
slower ball again, bounces just over the stumps. Malinga's cross-bat swipe gets nowhere near it.
a slower ball outside off stump, Malinga can't get bat to it
picked off his pads and timed well to the square leg fence. Another good shot, but coming too late for Sri Lanka, you feel

headshotImage.caption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: Kulasekara moves back, but Starc goes wide of the off stump. Wide is called, but it seems harsh as that was inside the tram lines.
fullish delivery on off stump, carved powerfully over the off side infield for four. Good shot. He's been trying it for a while
nicely flicked over short fine leg from Kulasekara, Picked up the short ball from leg stump and sent it high towards the boundary. The sweeper comes around to cut it off.
angled into the blockhole. Malinga digs it out and the batsmen take one.
full and angled in, Kulasekara knocks it down to long on

commentPreTextItems.html: Mitchell Starc is into the attack.

commentTextItems.html: nasty short ball angled into Malinga, and it looks like it's hit him on the glove. They take a run, but the physio is out there immediately.
yet another slower ball, Kulasekara, again, can't connect with a cut shot

107kph, Kualsekara advances but cant time his shot. Goes straight back to the bowler

slower short ball again, and Kulasekara sways out of the way, having misread the pace initially
